item.title: Report E-2024050692
item.description:
Report E-2024050692

Identified by scraper @ 2024-05-30T18:16:39+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-05-24
  • City: FALLSTON
  • State: MD
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: R & L CARRIERS, INC.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 4000
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: On May 24, 2024, one (1) 275-gallon tote of UN1170 was dropped and released approximately four (4) gallons of product to the concrete and soil. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from SMR Rapid Response, LLC (SMR) to remediate the impacted site. RLC advised the CES incident manager that all remediation and disposal would be completed by personnel at the customer location. SMR was advised to stand down as no further action would be needed. Photos were taken to document the scene and SMR personnel noted no further actions required on-site and demobilized.
